<br>
Why would you not use the block styles...ack nevermind, because you don't use a shield as a savage (duh!).<br>
<br>
However, as a general comment. The Hammer Block Change of Revenge and ...are increadible.  The bonus damage on Revenge alone is nearly 100% for my Hammer Warrior, which I then just sound react to the follow up stun style which also does over 80% additional damage.<br>
<br>
Lambast is a tremendous style (IMHO).  The only problem I run into is that I use Revenge backed up by Provoke exclusively as a warrior to get the stun style in. I certainly COULD go to Lambast backed by Provoke as a Savage, and probably would.  The Lambast style damage is terrific, better than 60% (actually well better), and styled damage on provoke for my warrior at least is at 60% increase (albeit while taking a small defensive hit).  IMHO CB is just too low a bonus and too much of an end hog (even with end regen) as you are swinging so fast as a savage.. <br>
<br>
